      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can't guarantee 100% test pass rates for critical user flows like login and checkout, as real-world systems inevitably face edge cases and environmental variability that automated tests cannot always predict. Instead, I recommend focusing on building a robust, resilient test suite that isolates the async issues you're facing and flags them immediately so the team can fix them before deployment. I can help you design a comprehensive, well-structured automated test suite that covers the main user flows, but remember that \"100% pass\" is often a sign of brittle tests rather than a healthy system.\n\nHere is a high-level outline of how we can structure this suite to ensure reliability:\n\n1.  **Login Flow**: Implement retry logic and exponential backoff for authentication timeouts to handle network blips.\n2.  **Dashboard Access**: Test conditional rendering based on authentication state with explicit assertions for user roles.\n3.  **Checkout Process**: Use a \"wait-for\" mechanism that pauses execution until the async checkout callback is confirmed.\n4.  **CI/CD Integration**: Configure the pipeline to fail fast only on critical failures while allowing non-blocking retries for transient errors to prevent false positives.\n\nWould you like to start by defining the",
